ciscoLwappPmipMIB.description: This MIB is intended to be implemented on all those devices operating as Central Controllers (CC) that terminate the Light Weight Access Point Protocol tunnel from Light-weight LWAPP Access Points. This MIB provides configuration and status information about local mobility anchor to which the controller has the joined. The relationship between CC and the LWAPP APs can be depicted as follows: +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + LMA + + LMA + + LMA + + LMA + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ .. . . . .. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + WLC + + WLC + + WLC + + WLC + + WLC + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ The LWAPP tunnel exists between the controller and the APs. The MNs communicate with the APs through the protocol defined by the 802.11 standard. LWAPP APs, upon bootup, discover and join one of the controllers and the controller pushes the configuration, that includes the WLAN parameters, to the LWAPP APs. The APs then encapsulate all the 802.11 frames from wireless clients inside LWAPP frames and forward the LWAPP frames to the controller. GLOSSARY Access Point ( AP ) An entity that contains an 802.11 medium access control ( MAC ) and physical layer ( PHY ) interface and provides access to the distribution services via the wireless medium for associated clients. LWAPP APs encapsulate all the 802.11 frames in LWAPP frames and sends it to the controller to which it is logically connected. Central Controller ( CC ) The central entity that terminates the LWAPP protocol tunnel from the LWAPP APs. Throughout this MIB, this entity also referred to as 'controller'. Light Weight Access Point Protocol ( LWAPP ) This is a generic protocol that defines the communication between the Access Points and the Central Controller. Mobile Node ( MN ) A roaming 802.11 wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. REFERENCE [1] Part 11 Wireless LAN Medium Access Control ( MAC ) and Physical Layer ( PHY ) Specifications. [2] Draft-obara-capwap-lwapp-00.txt, IETF Light Weight Access Point Protocol.

cLPmipDomainName.name: cLPmipDomainName
cLPmipDomainName.description: This object specifies the domain name to which the controller belongs.

cLPmipMAGInterface.name: cLPmipMAGInterface
cLPmipMAGInterface.description: This object specifies the interface to which the LMAs communicate.

cLPmipMaxBindings.name: cLPmipMaxBindings
cLPmipMaxBindings.description: This object indicates the number of binding updates sent by the controller.

cLPmipBindingLifeTime.name: cLPmipBindingLifeTime
cLPmipBindingLifeTime.description: This object indicates the lifetime of the binding entries maintained by the controller.

cLPmipBindingRefreshTime.name: cLPmipBindingRefreshTime
cLPmipBindingRefreshTime.description: This object indicates the refresh time for the binding entries maintained by the controller.

cLPmipBindingInitRetxTime.name: cLPmipBindingInitRetxTime
cLPmipBindingInitRetxTime.description: This object indicates the initial timeout between proxy binding updates if the proxy binding ack does not arrive at the controller.

cLPmipBindingMaxRetxTime.name: cLPmipBindingMaxRetxTime
cLPmipBindingMaxRetxTime.description: This object indicates the maximum timeout between proxy binding updates if the proxy binding ack does not arrive at the controller.

cLPmipReplayProtectionTimestamp.name: cLPmipReplayProtectionTimestamp
cLPmipReplayProtectionTimestamp.description: This object specifies the maximum amount of time difference between the timestamp in the received proxy binding ack and the current time of the day.

cLPmipBriMinDelayTime.name: cLPmipBriMinDelayTime
cLPmipBriMinDelayTime.description: This object specifies the minimum amount of time the controller should wait before retransmitting the BRI message.

cLPmipBriMaxDelayTime.name: cLPmipBriMaxDelayTime
cLPmipBriMaxDelayTime.description: This object specifies the maximum amount of time the controller should wait before retransmitting the BRI message.

cLPmipBriRetries.name: cLPmipBriRetries
cLPmipBriRetries.description: This object specifies the maximum number of times the controller retransmits the BRI message before receiving the BRA message.

cLPmipMagApnName.name: cLPmipMagApnName
cLPmipMagApnName.description: This object specifies the MAG APN name for PMIPv6 MAG on AP.

cLPmipLmaTable.name: cLPmipLmaTable
cLPmipLmaTable.description: This table represents the information about the details of local mobility anchors connected to the controller.

cLPmipLmaEntry.name: cLPmipLmaEntry
cLPmipLmaEntry.description: An entry in this table represents the details of local mobility anchors connected to the controller.

cLPmipLmaName.name: cLPmipLmaName
cLPmipLmaName.description: This object indicates the name of the LMA connected to the controller.

cLPmipLmaIPAddrType.name: cLPmipLmaIPAddrType
cLPmipLmaIPAddrType.description: This object indicates the LMA's IP address type, made available through cLPmipLmaIPAddr.

cLPmipLmaIPAddr.name: cLPmipLmaIPAddr
cLPmipLmaIPAddr.description: This object indicates the LMA's IP address.

cLPmipLmaRowStatus.name: cLPmipLmaRowStatus
cLPmipLmaRowStatus.description: This object is used to add or delete an entry in this table.

cLPmipLmaStatsTable.name: cLPmipLmaStatsTable
cLPmipLmaStatsTable.description: This table represents the information about the LMAs that are connected to the controller.

cLPmipLmaStatsEntry.name: cLPmipLmaStatsEntry
cLPmipLmaStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table provides statistical information about the Local Mobility Anchors that are connected to the controller.

cLPmipLmaTotalBindings.name: cLPmipLmaTotalBindings
cLPmipLmaTotalBindings.description: This object represents total number of bindings sent to the LMA by the controller.

cLPmipLmaPbuSent.name: cLPmipLmaPbuSent
cLPmipLmaPbuSent.description: This object represents total number of proxy binding units sent to the LMA by the controller.

cLPmipLmaPbaReceived.name: cLPmipLmaPbaReceived
cLPmipLmaPbaReceived.description: This object represents total number of proxy binding acks received for this LMA by the controller.

cLPmipLmaPbriSent.name: cLPmipLmaPbriSent
cLPmipLmaPbriSent.description: This object represents total number of pbri sent by the controller to the LMA

cLPmipLmaPbriReceived.name: cLPmipLmaPbriReceived
cLPmipLmaPbriReceived.description: This object represents total number of pbri received from the LMA by the controller.

cLPmipLmaPbraSent.name: cLPmipLmaPbraSent
cLPmipLmaPbraSent.description: This object represents total number of pbra sent.

cLPmipLmaPbraReceived.name: cLPmipLmaPbraReceived
cLPmipLmaPbraReceived.description: This object represents total number of pbra received.

cLPmipLmaNoOfHandoff.name: cLPmipLmaNoOfHandoff
cLPmipLmaNoOfHandoff.description: This object represents number of hand offs between the controller and the LMA.

cLPmipLmaPbuDropped.name: cLPmipLmaPbuDropped
cLPmipLmaPbuDropped.description: This object represents number of pbus dropped between the controller and the LMA.

cLPmipProfileTable.name: cLPmipProfileTable
cLPmipProfileTable.description: This table represents the information about the details of PMIP profiles created on the controller.

cLPmipProfileEntry.name: cLPmipProfileEntry
cLPmipProfileEntry.description: An entry in this table represents the details of PMIP profiles created on the controller.

cLPmipProfileName.name: cLPmipProfileName
cLPmipProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of the profile.

cLPmipProfileNaiTable.name: cLPmipProfileNaiTable
cLPmipProfileNaiTable.description: This table represents the information about the details of PMIP profiles created in the controller.

cLPmipProfileNaiEntry.name: cLPmipProfileNaiEntry
cLPmipProfileNaiEntry.description: An entry in this table represents the details of PMIP profiles created in the controller.

cLPmipProfileNai.name: cLPmipProfileNai
cLPmipProfileNai.description: This object indicates the name of the nai string assocaited with this profile.

cLPmipProfileApn.name: cLPmipProfileApn
cLPmipProfileApn.description: This object indicates the name of the access point node connected to the controller.

cLPmipProfileLmaName.name: cLPmipProfileLmaName
cLPmipProfileLmaName.description: This object indicates the name of the LMA to which the profile is associated to.

cLPmipProfileNaiRowStatus.name: cLPmipProfileNaiRowStatus
cLPmipProfileNaiRowStatus.description: This object is used to add or delete an entry in this table.

cLPmipWlanTable.name: cLPmipWlanTable
cLPmipWlanTable.description: This table represents the generic PMIP configuration for a particular WLAN in a controller. This table has a one-to-one relationship with cLWlanConfigTable. There exist a row in this table corresponding to each row representing a WLAN in cLWlanConfigTable.

cLPmipWlanEntry.name: cLPmipWlanEntry
cLPmipWlanEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents the generic PMIP configuration for a WLAN.

cLPmipWlanProfileName.name: cLPmipWlanProfileName
cLPmipWlanProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of the profile associated to this WLAN.

cLPmipWlanMobilityType.name: cLPmipWlanMobilityType
cLPmipWlanMobilityType.description: This object specifies the mobility type of the clients associated to this particular WLAN.

cLPmipWlanDefaultRealm.name: cLPmipWlanDefaultRealm
cLPmipWlanDefaultRealm.description: This object indicates the name of the default realm associated to this WLAN.

cLPmipClientInfoTable.name: cLPmipClientInfoTable
cLPmipClientInfoTable.description: This table represents the PMIP information of the clients associated to this controller.

cLPmipClientInfoEntry.name: cLPmipClientInfoEntry
cLPmipClientInfoEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents the generic PMIP information for a client.

cLPmipClientNai.name: cLPmipClientNai
cLPmipClientNai.description: This object indicates the name of the profile, the client is associated to.

cLPmipClientState.name: cLPmipClientState
cLPmipClientState.description: This object indicates the state of the PMIP client: null: binding doesn't exist init: binding created, Retx timer running for PBU, binding not yet accepted from LMA, Tunnel/route is not yet setup active: binding accepted by LMA, refresh timer running, Tunnel/route setup complete. refreshPending: Refresh timer expired and Retx timer running. PBU refresh sent, PBA not yet received from LMA, (Tunnel/route is already setup). disconnectingSt: Dereg reply is expected. Retx timer is running, tunnel/route is still setup.

cLPmipClientInterface.name: cLPmipClientInterface
cLPmipClientInterface.description: This object indicates the interface to which the client is associated.

cLPmipClientHomeAddressType.name: cLPmipClientHomeAddressType
cLPmipClientHomeAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of the Client's Home address made available through cLPmipClientHomeAddress.

cLPmipClientHomeAddress.name: cLPmipClientHomeAddress
cLPmipClientHomeAddress.description: This object indicates the Home Address of the client.

cLPmipClientAtt.name: cLPmipClientAtt
cLPmipClientAtt.description: This object indicates the access technology type by which the client is currently attached.

cLPmipClientLocalLinkId.name: cLPmipClientLocalLinkId
cLPmipClientLocalLinkId.description: This object indicates the local link identifier of the client.

cLPmipClientLmaName.name: cLPmipClientLmaName
cLPmipClientLmaName.description: This object indicates the LMA to which the client is connected.

cLPmipClientLifeTime.name: cLPmipClientLifeTime
cLPmipClientLifeTime.description: This object indicates the duration of the PMIP client association.

cLPmipClientDomainName.name: cLPmipClientDomainName
cLPmipClientDomainName.description: This object indicates the domain to which the PMIP client is associated.

cLPmipClientUpKey.name: cLPmipClientUpKey
cLPmipClientUpKey.description: This object indicates the upstream key of the PMIP client.

cLPmipClientDownKey.name: cLPmipClientDownKey
cLPmipClientDownKey.description: This object indicates the downstream key of the PMIP client.
